Fujian Forum Commemorates Taiwan Uprising
FUZHOU , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- A forum to mark the 51st anniversary of the Taiwan " February 28 Uprising " was held on Thursday in this capital of east China 's Fujian Province .
Representatives of Taiwan compatriots present said the purpose of commemorating the uprising was to draw lessons from history , promote patriotism and combat efforts to separate Taiwan from the rest of China or assert " Taiwan independence " .
At the same time , it was aimed at promoting cross-straits relations based on the principles of peaceful reunification and `` one country , two systems . "
The forum was sponsored by the Fujian Province Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League and the Federation of Taiwan Compatriots .
